"n.奴役，束缚 【英】 n. 奴役,束缚(slavery, captivity) 【记】 bond(绑)+age 【例】 keep sb in bondage n. 奴役(被迫做奴隸的状态), 束缚(屈从一种势力、权力或影响的状态) = slavery = captivity 【例】He is in bondage to his ambition 他被他的野心所支配. 【根】bond = serf(n 农奴, 奴隸) 【记】bond = band带, 绳－被绳子绑起来－束缚 【记】源自bind；音：绷带紧，绑得紧 bondage (n.)  c.1300, ""condition of a serf or slave,"" from Anglo-Latin bondagium, from Middle English bond ""a serf, tenant farmer,"" from Old English bonda ""householder,"" from Old Norse boandi ""free-born farmer,"" noun use of present participle of boa ""dwell, prepare, inhabit,"" from PIE *bhow-, from root *bheue- ""to be, exist, dwell"" (see be). Meaning in English changed by influence of bond. The sexual sado-masochism sense is recorded by 1966."
